# World & Vehicles Context

You are working on the world/scene layout or driving system. Read these docs:

1. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` — shared patterns
2. `docs/design/world-and-vehicles.md` — world layout, instanced scenes, vehicles, driving
3. `docs/design/world-and-scenes.md` — scene topology and migration contract
4. `docs/design/world-scene-contracts.md` — required world-scene wiring/validation guardrails
5. `docs/design/extensible-development-contracts.md` — integration workflows (scene/checkpoint/interactable/NPC/save touchpoints)

If your scene task also modifies gameplay/UI systems in the same change, load the corresponding domain docs for those systems.

For scene/component wiring changes:
- use deterministic wiring tools where available
- perform MCP read-back verification for changed scene objects/components
- run targeted world scene contract tests before claiming completion

For local world/vehicle runtime or test cleanup, use `.cursor/rules/world-vehicles-runtime-local-context.mdc` instead.

Do NOT load reloading-domain-knowledge, accuracy calculations, or other unrelated deep domain docs unless the task explicitly crosses into them.
